HEADWORD: Agalmatolite
<hw>Ag`al*mat"o*lite</hw>
<pr>(⟦acr⟧g`⟦acr⟧l*m⟦acr⟧t"⟦osl⟧*l⟦imac⟧t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>'a`galma</grk>, <grk>'a`galmatos</grk>, image, statue +
<ets>-lite</ets>: cf. F. <ets>agalmatolithe</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A soft, compact stone, of a grayish, greenish, or
yellowish color, carved into images by the Chinese, and hence called
<altname>figure stone</altname>, and <altname>pagodite</altname>. It is
probably a variety of pinite.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Agama</ent>⟦br⟧
